# MS-CLIENT

## Description

This microservice manages client information.

It provides CRUD operations for clients and integrates with other services using event-driven architecture.

---

## Architecture

The project follows Hexagonal Architecture:

- domain: business models and rules
- application: use cases and orchestration
- infrastructure: controllers, persistence, kafka, configuration

---

## Technologies

- Java 21
- Spring Boot
- JPA (PostgreSQL)
- Flyway
- Kafka
- Lombok
- OpenAPI
- Resilience4j

---

## How to Run Locally

### 1. Run application

./gradlew bootRun

---

### 2. Access API

http://localhost:8080

---

### 3. Swagger

http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html

---

## Endpoints

### Clients

- POST /clients
- GET /clients
- GET /clients/{id}
- PUT /clients/{id}
- DELETE /clients/{id}

---

## Database

- Managed with Flyway
- Migrations located in:
  src/main/resources/db/migration

---

## Seed Data

- Initial clients are loaded automatically via Flyway

---

## Testing

Run:

./gradlew test

---

## Docker

Build image:

docker build -t ms-client .

Run container:

docker run -p 8080:8080 ms-client

---

## Notes

- No hardcoded values
- Configuration via application.yml
